= Flower Structure and Cross-Pollination

- **Cross-Pollination**: Pollen from different individual. Increases genetic diversity.
- **Self-Pollination**: Pollen from same flower or plant. Similar to asexual reproduction genetically.

== Mechanisms Promoting Cross-Pollination

- **Stamen and Style Maturation Times**: Protandry (anthers first) or Protogyny (stigmas first).
- **Self-Incompatibility**: Chemical barriers preventing self-pollen growth.
- **Dioecy**: Separate staminate (male) and carpellate (female) plants.
- **Monoecy**: Separate staminate and carpellate flowers on the same plant (e.g., corn).

